 "lrc": "[00:07.44]This is for the ones nobody checks on\n[00:12.08]because they look like they got it together.\n[00:16.00]Bills paid. Kids fed. Smile ready.\n[00:20.56]But somewhere between Queens and Brooklyn,\n[00:24.16]under the elevated,\n[00:26.64]somebody is asking:\n[00:29.52]“Is this really addiction?”\n[00:32.00]You work hard.\n[00:34.96]You deserve peace.\n[00:38.24]Come here...\n[00:49.44]Queens Boulevard got my promises,\n[00:54.32]Brooklyn nights got my shame.\n[00:56.64]I keep showing up like I’m solid,\n[00:58.80]but I keep coming home the same.\n[01:02.16]Rent paid, lights on, fridge full,\n[01:05.76]everybody thinks I’m blessed.\n[01:07.76]I keep my body right, keep my money good,\n[01:10.64]still got smoke inside my chest.\n[01:13.92]Corner store glowing like a chapel,\n[01:16.96]midnight glass behind the door.\n[01:19.84]I tell myself I’m only looking,\n[01:22.88]but my hand already knows.\n[01:25.28]Long day.\n[01:26.72]Don’t make it deep.\n[01:28.24]One little flame.\n[01:29.68]One little drink.\n[01:30.96]One little sleep.\n[01:33.68]And it don’t feel like addiction,\n[01:38.72]it feels like I’m still in control.\n[01:41.28]Like I could stop when I’m ready,\n[01:44.88]like I could leave it alone.\n[01:46.96]I quit three days just to prove it,\n[01:50.24]then came back like I won.\n[01:52.32]But that ain’t freedom,\n[01:53.92]that’s just losing with a different kind of gun.\n[01:58.08]The cage don’t always rattle.\n[02:00.48]Sometimes it sings.\n[02:01.60]I’m chasing the dragon under the elevated,\n[02:05.68]trying to catch what don’t come back no more.\n[02:08.96]First time flew, now I’m stuck here waiting\n[02:11.60]with my heart face down on the floor.\n[02:13.96]It don’t feel like addiction,\n[02:15.92]it feels like tomorrow.\n[02:17.36]Feels like one more night,\n[02:18.56]feels like borrowed sorrow.\n[02:21.00]I wanna quit,\n[02:21.44]but I want that fire.\n[02:23.20]I want the truth,\n[02:24.32]but I love the liar.\n[02:26.48]And the dragon don’t fly no more.\n[02:30.80]On the J train with my jaw tight,\n[02:33.60]on the 7 with my head low.\n[02:37.04]Every ad says buy your freedom,\n[02:39.84]every craving says don’t let go.\n[02:42.00]I got side dreams, side gigs,\n[02:44.48]plans folded in my notes.\n[02:47.68]But I keep feeding little habits\n[02:50.24]that keep standing on my throat.\n[02:52.88]I say “next week” like a prayer,\n[02:55.52]say “last time” like a song.\n[02:57.12]Say “I’m good” when I’m lying,\n[02:58.56]say “I’m fine” when I’m gone.\n[03:00.32]Gone?\n[03:01.12]Baby, you’re here.\n[03:02.80]I’m the only thing clear\n[03:05.60]when the city gets heavy.\n[03:08.40]I disappear your fear.\n[03:10.88]You call me poison,\n[03:12.40]but I call you mine.\n[03:13.76]You call it weakness,\n[03:15.28]I call it time.\n[03:16.64]Don’t call me yours.\n[03:18.64]Then why do you answer?\n[03:21.20]Addiction don’t always kick the door in.\n[03:24.32]Sometimes it uses your own voice.\n[03:27.04]Sometimes it says,\n[03:28.88]“You earned this.”\n[03:30.08]At the counter with the music low,\n[03:32.72]card in my hand, heart in my throat.\n[03:35.52]I ask myself, “Do I need this?”\n[03:37.84]then laugh like it’s some kind of joke.\n[03:40.88]What else could I do with this money?\n[03:43.04]What else could I do with this pain?\n[03:46.56]What man keeps building a future\n[03:49.44]then burning the bridge in the rain?\n[03:51.60]I’m chasing the dragon under the elevated,\n[03:55.68]trying to catch what don’t come back no more.\n[03:58.56]I can make it feel close.\n[03:59.68]I can open that door.\n[04:03.04]It don’t feel like addiction,\n[04:05.28]it feels like tomorrow.\n[04:06.64]Feels like one more night,\n[04:08.16]feels like borrowed sorrow.\n[04:10.32]Borrow it, baby.\n[04:11.68]You can pay it later.\n[04:13.60]And the dragon don’t fly no more.\n[04:16.48]To the one saying “I can stop”\n[04:19.44]but never really stops:\n[04:21.92]this is the sign.\n[04:22.88]Not shame.\n[04:23.60]Not judgment.\n[04:24.32]Come back home.\n[04:26.80]Do I really need this?\n[04:28.24]Do I really want this?\n[04:29.68]Am I really free\n[04:30.64]if I keep running from the honest?\n[04:32.48]Do I want to stop,\n[04:33.76]or do I want to hide?\n[04:35.04]Do I want my life back,\n[04:36.48]or another alibi?\n[04:38.16]Nobody knows you like I know you.\n[04:40.80]Nobody holds you like I hold you.\n[04:44.08]That’s not love.\n[04:45.04]That’s not peace.\n[04:46.48]That’s you taking little pieces out of me.\n[04:49.36]I don’t need to hit bottom\n[04:50.72]just to prove the bottom’s real.\n[04:52.00]I don’t need another bottle\n[04:53.60]just to tell me how to feel.\n[04:54.96]Help me.\n[04:55.76]Hear me.\n[04:56.48]I’m still in here.\n[04:57.92]Don’t fear me.\n[04:59.36]I look alright,\n[05:00.72]but I’m not okay.\n[05:02.16]I keep surviving,\n[05:04.00]but I wanna change.\n[05:07.20]Call me.\n[05:07.52]Hold me.\n[05:09.44]Don’t shame me.\n[05:10.10]Just know me.\n[05:11.28]I need love.\n[05:11.84]I need truth.\n[05:14.16]I need somebody\n[05:16.56]to pull me through.\n[05:18.96]One more night.\n[05:20.40]One more flame.\n[05:21.76]One more pour.\n[05:22.80]I’m not chasing the dragon under the elevated,\n[05:26.24]not tonight, not like before.\n[05:28.80]First time’s gone and I’m done here waiting\n[05:31.92]for a ghost to give me more.\n[05:33.60]It did feel like addiction\n[05:35.76]when I finally saw the chain.\n[05:37.52]It did feel like a prison\n[05:39.84]when I called it by its name.\n[05:44.16]I wanna live\n[05:45.28]more than I want that fire.\n[05:47.68]I want the truth\n[05:49.28]more than I want the liar.\n[05:52.16]And the dragon don’t fly no more.\n[05:56.64]You’ll miss me by morning.\n[05:58.08]Maybe I will.\n[05:59.44]You’ll call me when it hurts.\n[06:00.88]I’ll call someone real.\n[06:02.88]You’ll come back to me.\n[06:04.08]Not this time.\n[06:05.20]For anybody fighting quiet:\n[06:08.64]you are not the thing you’re fighting.\n[06:10.64]Cry out.\n[06:12.16]Reach out.\n[06:12.88]Come back.\n[06:13.76]The night is loud,\n[06:14.88]but you are louder.\n[06:16.48]Help me.\n[06:16.96]I’m ready.\n[06:17.92]One more...\n[06:22.48]No.\n"
}